              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Pillar</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Pillar II — Apex: Own Your Nature</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Tenet</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Tenet V — Protect Those Beneath You.</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-body">Strength that only serves itself isn't strength — it's hoarding. Apex means the top. And the top has responsibilities.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Lineage</div>
                <p class="workflow-quote">"Accept the things to which fate binds you, and love the people with whom fate brings you together, and do so with all your heart."</p>
                <div class="workflow-cite">— Marcus Aurelius, Meditations, Book VI</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">Your Practice</div>
                <p class="workflow-action">Ask yourself who in your life needs you to speak up for them. Write their name down. Find a way to use your influence — a conversation, a call, a door you can open — to make their situation better.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-links">
              <a href="/tenets#tenet-v" class="workflow-link">Read Tenet V →</a>
              <a href="/lineage" class="workflow-link">Read the Lineage →</a>
              <a href="/practice" class="workflow-link">Today's Practice →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="situation-card reveal d4">
        <button class="situation-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="situation-label">"I keep telling myself I'm a victim of my circumstances."</span>
          <span class="situation-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" /></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="situation-answer">
          <div class="situation-answer-inner">
            <div class="workflow">
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Pillar</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Pillar II — Apex: Own Your Nature</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Tenet</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Tenet VI — Reject the Victim. Become the Author.</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-body">Wearing hardship as an identity gives the worst moments of your life permanent control over the rest of it.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Lineage</div>
                <p class="workflow-quote">"It's not what happens to you, but how you react to it that matters."</p>
                <div class="workflow-cite">— Epictetus, Discourses</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">Your Practice</div>
                <p class="workflow-action">Write down the story you keep telling yourself. Then write the version where you're the one who overcame it. Live that one.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-links">
              <a href="/tenets#tenet-vi" class="workflow-link">Read Tenet VI →</a>
              <a href="/lineage" class="workflow-link">Read the Lineage →</a>
              <a href="/practice" class="workflow-link">Today's Practice →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="situation-card reveal d5">
        <button class="situation-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="situation-label">"I feel stuck — like I can't level up no matter what I do."</span>
          <span class="situation-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2.5" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4.5v15m7.5-7.5h-15" /></svg></span>
        </button>
        <div class="situation-answer">
          <div class="situation-answer-inner">
            <div class="workflow">
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Pillar</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Pillar II — Apex: Own Your Nature</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Tenet</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-title">Tenet IV — Never Shrink. Never Apologize for Strength.</div>
                <div class="workflow-step-body">Stuck usually means comfortable. The ceiling you're hitting is the one you built. Remove it.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">The Lineage</div>
                <p class="workflow-quote">"No man is free who is not master of himself."</p>
                <div class="workflow-cite">— Epictetus, Discourses</div>
              </div>
              <div class="workflow-step active-step">
                <div class="workflow-step-label">Your Practice</div>
                <p class="workflow-action">Identify the one skill, conversation, or risk that would change your trajectory. Start it before the day ends.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="workflow-links">
              <a href="/tenets#tenet-iv" class="workflow-link">Read Tenet IV →</a>
              <a href="/lineage" class="workflow-link">Read the Lineage →</a>
              <a href="/practice" class="workflow-link">Today's Practice →</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
